    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-19T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="340"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d340">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/297b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-19T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 19, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2081. Department has authorized <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName>,
                    who is now at Yokohama, to return with <persName corresp="#p_ECH1">Colonel
                        Emerson</persName> and his party to Harbin and <pb facs="0272" n="222"
                        xml:id="pg_222"/> to commence their efforts from that point, working both
                    toward Vladivostok and also westwards.</p>
                <p>Original friendly purpose of these experienced American railway operators to
                    assist Russian railway authorities modified in no particular. <persName
                        corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> will notify you when he arrives
                    Harbin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
